================================================================================
ORIGINAL DESIGNS AND CONCEPTS
================================================================================

The following designs, features, and architectural patterns were originated
by the EchoBird project. The source code that implements them is governed
by the AGPL-3.0 license; the underlying ideas are documented here so that
downstream forks and reimplementations can credit prior art appropriately.

  1. Mother Agent (internal codename) / 安装与修复 (user-facing UI name)
     — An AI-driven flow that installs and repairs AI coding tools, agents,
     and CLIs. Supports both local and remote execution targets.
     First public commit: 2026-03-02 (src/pages/MotherAgent.tsx, 1410 lines
     at commit 546a14ae).

  2. Model Nexus / 模型中心 — "Configure once, used everywhere"
     A unified model data hub architecture where a single set of model
     configurations (API key, base URL, model ID, protocol) drives multiple
     distinct user-facing scenarios (Install & Repair, Local LLM, My AI
     Projects, App Manager) without any per-scenario re-configuration.
     First public commit: 2026-03-02 (initial model directory and icons);
     dedicated "Model Nexus" naming: 2026-03-26.

  3. 我的AI项目 / My AI Projects
     A user-facing flow for managing vibe-coded apps and games with
     per-project model assignment. Each user project lives as its own card
     in EchoBird with editable model bindings and a one-click launch.
     First public commit: 2026-05-20 (src/pages/MyProjects/).

  4. 应用管理 / App Manager
     A one-click launch and management panel for AI / Agent applications
     and games. Tools are registered via paths.json metadata; the same UI
     handles install, model swap, and launch with no terminal interaction.
     First public commit: 2026-03-02 (src/pages/AppManager.tsx, 674 lines
     at commit 546a14ae).

  5. Codex Translator with Spec-Pure Passthrough
     A Responses ↔ Chat Completions translator (and Anthropic Messages
     equivalent) that deliberately forwards only OpenAI-spec-canonical
     fields and refuses per-vendor shimming for upstream non-compliance.
     The refusal to shim is treated as a feature, not a limitation — it
     keeps the natural feedback chain to vendors intact and avoids
     accumulating tech debt from speculative compatibility layers.
     First public commit: 2026-03-04 onward (originally under
     tools/codex/, later moved to src-tauri/src/services/codex_proxy/).

